item.title: Base Metals Recover After US Debt Worries, Sluggish China Demand Hit Prices
item.description: Base metals were higher, with gold flat, in early London trade, as worries over the U.S. debt ceiling and Chinese demand continued to drag on markets.

item.title: Siemens's 2Q Orders, Revenue Growth Offset Healthineers Weakness
item.description: Siemens orders and revenue in the second quarter increased and exceeded consensus estimates, Bernstein said, and thinks investors should react positively to the results.

item.title: Siemens Outperforms in Second Quarter, Lifts Outlook
item.description: Siemens posted an above-forecast net result in the second quarter, as profits at its industrial businesses hit a record €2.6 billion, and upgraded its guidance for the year.

item.title: EU New Car Sales Lifted by EV Demand
item.description: EU car registrations rose 17% year-on-year in April, with sales of fully electric cars up 52%.

item.title: Limited Relative Value Seen in Germany's February 2033 Bund Pre-Auction
item.description: Germany’s 2.30% February 2033 Bund, which will be reopened at an auction later on Wednesday, offers limited relative value, according to Citi.

item.title: Dollar Rises on China Slowdown Fears, Improved US Data
item.description: The dollar hit a five-week high against a basket of currencies due to concerns about a slowing Chinese economy, which is weighing heavily on Asian and Latin American currencies, MUFG said.

item.title: Chinese Companies Looked to Switzerland to Sell Shares---Things Haven't Been Great
item.description: An expanded stock link between exchanges in China and Europe has helped companies raise money, but trading is anemic and prices have fallen.

item.title: Munich Re Upbeat on Full Year After Renewals Boost
item.description: Munich Re posted an above-forecast net profit in the first quarter and said it still expected a net result of about EUR4 billion for the 2023 but that profitable growth confirmed by its reinsurance renewals as of April 1 mean the chances of surpassing that target have increased.

item.title: Aegon Confident on Strategy and Outlook
item.description: Aegon reported a 5% rise in operating capital generation for the first quarter of 2023 and said it was confident of delivering on its financial guidance for the year.

item.title: UBS Plans for $4 Billion Legal Hit From Credit Suisse Deal
item.description: The Swiss bank released new details about the acquisition’s likely impact on its balance sheet.

item.title: Commerzbank Outlook on Track as Profits Jump
item.description: Commerzbank confirmed its guidance for the year after reporting higher-than-expected profit and core revenues for the first quarter, helped by higher interest rates.

item.title: Haunted by Hiroshima, Japanese Leader to Meet Biden With a Push for No Nukes
item.description: Japanese Prime Minister Fumio Kishida has said ridding the world of nuclear weapons is his life’s work, but the task looks ever more difficult as he gathers world leaders in Hiroshima.

item.title: The Case of the Vanishing Vacation Flights
item.description: Budget airlines like Avelo, Breeze and Frontier frequently experiment with flights and yank them quickly if they don’t perform.
